content: Sent on behalf of Triton Engineering Student Council (TESC) Fall quarter is almost over, and that means that the Disciplines of Engineering Career Fair (Decaf) is just around the corner! Decaf will be during week 2 of winter quarter, on Thursday, January 16, 2020 from 8AM to 2PM at the Price Center Ballrooms (East & West). Decaf is the largest student-run engineering career fair at UC San Diego. This event gives you the opportunity to meet, impress, and get hired by top engineering companies. Coming to the career fair increases your chances of landing internships, summer positions or permanent employment opportunities. Don’t miss out on this chance to talk to professionals who share your interests!

Happy and healthy Winter! Just a reminder that you have until January 18th, 2019 to officially add First Year Experience (“MUIR 1”). All new Freshmen are pre-authorized to enroll, so all that is needed is to add the course via WebReg at https://act.ucsd.edu/webreg2. Enrollment is limited to 24 students, but currently our Friday 12pm Discussion Section (Section ID 963594) has a little space. Below you will find messages from members of the instructional team (Faculty, Discussion Leader) about their upcoming course and their goals. We hope you will consider joining us!

Hello Sixth College Residents! We hope your winter breaks are winding up productively and that you’re looking forward to a great winter quarter! We wanted to send a final reminder to you that the 19-20 RA Applications are still live and remain open until January 8th at 2pm! That is a very strict cut off time so don’t wait to get your application in as we will not make exceptions if your application is late! We look forward to seeing your applications and learning more about you! Please direct all questions about your application to the front desk of the residential areas you apply to, you can access their information here http://reslifeapp.ucsd.edu/

points.text: RA Applications are still live and remain open

content: Triton Actuarial Society (TAS) is holding its first meeting of the Winter quarter on Friday, January 11th, 2019 from 3:13 p.m. - 5:00 p.m. at Roosevelt College Room in Price Center. There will be a guest speaker, David Kim, FSA, from Cigna Health Insurance as well. As the next academic year officer recruitment is coming up, we will give an overview of the recruitment process and a brief description of each officer position at the meeting. David Kim will give us an info session followed by a Q&A session. This will be a great opportunity to network with actuarial professional, so don't miss out. Resumes will be welcomed.
